  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hello to the community of developers. I am worried about something: There are almost empty blocks (less than 30 tx) being mined on the blockchain since the London hardfork block. All of them have in common that the included trasactions have a high gas limit but, with a very low gas consumption. It is posible that setting a high gas limit to normal trasactions, could be used to intentionally attack the network by generating almost empty blocks to produce congestion?\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/block/12966835\r\nIn this block the total gas limit was 28,601,046 gwei but the gas consumption was 1,920,428",
