    "body": "> All of them have in common that the included transactions have a high gas limit but, with a very low gas consumption\r\n\r\nIn this case, the remaining gas can be used for the next transaction. It's not the attack.\r\n\r\nFor the small block, either the basefee is high enough so that users can not afford the cost, or the mining pools refuse to pack more transactions. It's the choice of mining pool since they lose some transaction fee.",
